{
  "_doc": "Magic: The Gathering | Marvel Super Heroes (code MSH) — Universes Beyond set, released 2026-06-26. Source: https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-marvel-super-heroes . Lineup is Play Boosters + Collector Boosters (plus Jumpstart/Commander products we don't model as packs) — no Draft Boosters, hence authoritative:true. Percentages are taken verbatim from the article's odds tables, which give per-slot shares; the two per-PACK phrasings are converted to per-slot weights: scene commons '8.6% of boosters' -> 8.6/7 = 1.2 per common slot, source material '1 out of 24 Play Boosters' -> (100/24)/7 = 0.6 per common slot, scene uncommons '12%' -> 12/3 = 4 per uncommon slot. Sub-percentages reported as 'less than 1%' are entered as 0.5; the 'extremely low quantity' textless cosmic-foil Mind Stone is 0.1, mirroring spm.json's Soul Stone convention. MSC reprint vs new-to-Magic Jumpstart sub-splits are merged into single MSC outcomes at the combined rate (both halves live in the same Scryfall set, indistinguishable by filter); 'Welcome Deck mythic' folded into the MSC mythic share. City calm & chaos full-art basics -> 'full_art_basic' merged into one pool because Scryfall doesn't distinguish calm from chaos and both appear at identical rates (article rates summed: 10+10 nonfoil, 2.5+2.5 foil in the Play land slot); regular basics -> 'non_full_art_basic'. Source Material -> exact: set MAR (Marvel Universe) + 'msh_source_material' (collector 41-100, the 60-card MSH-era sheet; 1-40 belong to SPM). AUDIT 2026-07 #2 (the big one): the preview-era filter mappings were WRONG against the released pool and made Collector packs shower chase mythics. Scryfall did NOT tag MSH's scenes promo_types:'poster' the way it tagged SPM's — only 3 prints carry 'poster', and they are CLASSIC COMIC chase mythics (Doctor Doom #394, Namor #391, Captain America #387), so every 'scene_card' outcome (including the GUARANTEED foil scene slot in Collector) pulled one of the set's 3 most expensive cards, and 'showcase' only matched the 17 panel cards so Logo/Panel/Classic-Comic outcomes all pulled panels. The released pool identifies every Booster Fun sheet by collector-number block instead, with rarity censuses matching the article exactly: panel 297-313 (11R/6M), SCENE 314-351 (3C/12U/8R/15M — the real 38 scenes; the 5 modal_dfc are the double-sided dinner scene), logo 352-379 (15R/13M, 5 modal_dfc), borderless dual lands 380-384 (5R), cosmic-foil Mind Stone 385 (promo_types:cosmicfoil -> 'cosmic_foil'), Gauntlet Mind Stone 386, classic comic 387-401 (15, 4 modal_dfc; article says all mythic though Scryfall lists 4 as rare — msh_classic_comic therefore carries no rarity leaf), extended art 402-429 (24R/4M, excluding the 431/432 bundle promos). All outcomes now use the msh_* CN-block filters from data/filters.json, and the aggregate scene/logo/panel weights are split into the article's exact per-rarity shares (wildcard, rare/mythic, foil, and both Collector booster-fun slots). The Collector guaranteed foil scene slot is the article's 20% common / 80% uncommon — a cheap mural piece, not a chase mythic. 'Scene Box borderless card' (13.9% non-foil booster fun) has no distinct Scryfall prints — the two Scene Box products' 12 cards are drawn from the same 38-card borderless scene sheet — so that outcome pulls msh_scene at any rarity; closest faithful mapping, revisit if Scryfall ever catalogues the box cards separately.",
